<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/32069202-kathleen"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1489076943i/32069202._UX100_CR0,15,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/32069202-kathleen">Kathleen</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">For me, I would say there is no similarity to the Wheel of Time. I loved the Wheel of Time series for its characters, world building, and strong femal<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">For me, I would say there is no similarity to the Wheel of Time. I loved the Wheel of Time series for its characters, world building, and strong females. I have only read The Summer Tree so far and would liken it to Tolkien, while I have actually found the book more mystical than either. I have loved the atmosphere created by Guy Gavriel Kay which has elevated the story telling to amazing heights.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
