              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/31691644-jaya?shelf=ahhh-die-gef%C3%BChle">ahhh-die-gefühle</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/31691644-jaya?shelf=audio">audio</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/31691644-jaya?shelf=sci-fi-fantasy-magic">sci-fi-fantasy-magic</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/31691644-jaya?shelf=did-we-read-the-same-book">did-we-read-the-same-book</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/31691644-jaya?shelf=mmxix">mmxix</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2681311319" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14920465075576425222">2.75⭐<br/>Took me the better part of a year to finish this one. <br/>Except for the ever grieving character of Paul, nothing/no one in particular worked for me, unfortunately. <br/>A classic case of its-not-you-but-me. <br/>Would I continue with the series? Maybe. Someday.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


