Zeynel encounters a lost traveller in red. He wakes up the next day discovering, with horror, that he is the victim of a blood-sucking djinni. Now a djinni himself, he returns home, seeking to reconcile his faith and former human identity with his new life. The biggest concern for Zeynel however is what this all means for Ayşe, and he fears, more than anything, to one day say goodbye to the woman who is his entire world. \n\nTold in two books, Volume I weaves a tapestry of Zeynel and Ayse\'s life, from their beginnings as wide-eyed, insecure teenagers in an Anatolian village, to their struggle 30 years later in the aftermath of Zeynel\'s death as a vampire. With a gentle and compassionate voice, this historical epic will break and heal you, and make you a home between its arabesque pages.\n\nRead online here: http://reimenayee.com/the-carpet-merchant-of-konstantiniyya/\nHardback edition soon to be published by Unbound.<\/span>\n  <a data-text-id=\"8284737901048574851\" href=\"#\" onclick=\"swapContent(\$(this));; return false;\">...more<\/a>\n\n    <\/div>\n\n      <div class=\'wtrButtonContainer wtrSignedOut\' id=\'24_book_39976610\'>\n<div class=\'wtrUp wtrLeft\'>\n<form action=\"/shelf/add_to_shelf\" accept-charset=\"UTF-8\" method=\"post\"><input name=\"utf8\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"&#x2713;\" /><input type=\"hidden\" name=\"authenticity_token\" value=\"tGqnIfW07+dNV2Wq1jQ3W0nYYoonMeOZoQyvwH/dHwZj00Ce0+WqR7W0/Ig4UgmGsIYpd0sRxrGe2jKfor+jLQ==\" />\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"book_id\" id=\"book_id\" value=\"39976610\" />\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"name\" id=\"name\" value=\"to-read\" />\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"unique_id\" id=\"unique_id\" value=\"24_book_39976610\" />\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"wtr_new\" id=\"wtr_new\" value=\"true\" />\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"from_choice\" id=\"from_choice\" value=\"false\" />\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"from_home_module\" id=\"from_home_module\" value=\"false\" />\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"ref\"